name: Drug and Alcohol Test
description: First time drivers course provider in FL
overview:
If you’re looking to get a Florida Driver’s License, the State of Florida requires all applicants to complete and pass a Learner’s Permit course. This course is also known as Traffic Law and Substance Abuse Education (TLSAE) and the 4-Hour Drug & Alcohol Course. It doesn’t really matter what you call it, this is the State-Approved course you need at the price you’ve been looking for.

At Drugandalcoholtest.com we’re happy to provide our students with a fun and easy learning experience. Our 4-Hour Learner’s Permit course can be completed online, in the comfort of your own home, or anywhere you can find a computer with an internet connection.
